{{Noticebox/Community}}
This guide explains how to set up and use '''[[Community:ShaderMotion|ShaderMotion]]''' to record avatar motion in VRChat and export it as Unity animation files. ShaderMotion is a shader-based motion-to-video codec that encodes humanoid bone rotations into video color blocks. It can be used to record performances, create animations for worlds, and stream motion for live events.

